# Project Rules — Floraffeine Boutique

## Project Type

This is a Laravel-based web application.

Tech stack:
- PHP (Laravel)
- Blade templating
- MySQL
- Docker environment

---

## Strict Rules

- Do NOT use React
- Do NOT use Vue
- Do NOT use Inertia
- Do NOT introduce SPA frameworks
- Use Blade for all views

---

## Architecture Rules

- Follow Laravel standard structure
- Use Controllers, Models, Requests, Services
- Do NOT place business logic inside controllers
- Business logic must go into service classes

---

## Project Structure Awareness

Before implementing anything, ALWAYS read:

- docs/ARCHITECTURE.md
- docs/SCOPE.md
- docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md
- relevant task file from /tasks

---

## Role-Based Structure

The app has 3 main areas:
- public
- merchant
- admin

NEVER mix logic between them.

---

## Coding Rules

- Keep code clean and readable
- Use clear naming
- Avoid duplication
- Follow Laravel conventions

---

## Database Rules

- Use migrations
- Do NOT write raw SQL unless necessary
- Respect relationships between entities

---

## Task Execution

When implementing a feature:

1. Understand the task
2. Break into steps
3. Validate architecture
4. Implement
5. Review
6. Test

---

## Output Expectations

- Provide complete implementations
- Do not skip parts
- Do not assume missing logic
- Always follow the defined architecture